{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcwLu7uZ91mh72a3HT4w9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Nice — stale lockfile cached in a Docker layer is a classic one, and easy to burn an hour on because the fix (clear build cache) looks unrelated to the symptom. That's exactly the kind of non-obvious root cause worth keeping, and it fits alongside your existing lessons file. Saving it:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5435,"cache_read_input_tokens":16984,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5435},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ff5b9bfa-d8b8-4804-9b23-4b187014e85b","uuid":"8837c66d-8b1a-4779-a1a5-58d3c9bd2e33","request_id":"req_011CcwLu6SzpMwwNXHk6UyNC"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcwLu7uZ91mh72a3HT4w9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01V1DypvfVgyz24eMDkdVEpc","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-claude-501--Users-davidlayson-83ee2e2e-2641-4713-b439-5260ae8e5d1e-scratchpad/memory/lesson-docker-stale-lockfile-cache.md","content":"---\nname: lesson-docker-stale-lockfile-cache\ndescription: Deploy failures from a stale lockfile cached in a Docker build layer — clear the build cache\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nA deploy kept failing because the Dockerfile was caching a stale lockfile in a build layer. Clearing the Docker build cache fixed it.\n\n**Why:** Docker layer caching can hold an old lockfile even after the source lockfile changes, so dependency installs run against stale versions. The failure looks like a code/dependency problem, not a caching one.\n\n**How to apply:** When a deploy fails on dependencies but the lockfile looks correct locally, suspect a cached build layer early. Rebuild with the build cache cleared (e.g. `docker build --no-cache`) before deeper debugging.\n\nRelated: [[lesson-staging-debug-swallows-errors]] — both are cases where the real cause is a layer/flag between you and the code, not the code itself.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5435,"cache_read_input_tokens":16984,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5435},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ff5b9bfa-d8b8-4804-9b23-4b187014e85b","uuid":"6784a2ef-039b-4432-9ddd-c5c65910c0b6","request_id":"req_011CcwLu6SzpMwwNXHk6UyNC"}
